, the crisis was resolved by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../230/58230.xml">
Solon</link>'s reforms, which eliminated <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../815/91815.xml">
debt bondage</link> and protected the peasant class. Nonetheless, the Greek aristocrat's domains remained small compared with the Roman <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../649/483649.xml">
latifundia</link></it>.</p>

